comment:
@alexmatsalehthank you so much for your kind words, Alex. When I reflect back on my life I see the tremendous but subtle forces of chance and luck. I met my wife by sheer chance, and followed her to Malaysia. Things could have worked out in a billion other ways, but I was lucky. That is the only way I can begin to understand the mystery of how things come together and separate.
I hope you find satisfaction in your work as a hairdresser. You must come into contact with many people, and each person is a window into something potentially miraculous. So much depends, not on what is in front of us, but how we see what is in front of us. Most of us are like blind people wandering around in the Louvre.
Often the grass is greener on the other side because it is Astro turf. Wherever you are is fine, if you are.

